author: Wan Xin Tan
text:
Home gym for many years but recently my card was auto terminated by UOB (when i was overseas) & this was how AF does their customer service.

firstly, i was expected to contact vendor myself.

secondly, i was expected to update AF when my flight come back from work trip was already 30/5 AM.

Business dont seem to know the importance of retaining customers. but that's fine, to AF it always seem like its our fault :). Will not recommend any of my friends to sign up here anymore & we are migrating our home gym!

I've been trying to reach them on WhatsApp for months, but responses have dwindled to almost nothing, so 3 stars from me.

author: Munny L
text:
Every equipment you'll ever need.
Inbody analysis available.
Vending machine full of protein and protein bars.

Cardio section, threadmills, elliptical, cycles and a single stairmaster. 2 squat racks and 1 smith machine

Free weights (dumbbells) and barbell weights with a bench press. Integrated heavy duty machines that combines row and lat pulldowns.

Workout mats at your disposal, kettle bell and even TRX bands. And resistance bands. Even foam rollers. Yoga ball x 2.

Assisted pull ups, Upperbody machines followed by lower body machines.
Leg press x 2
Leg curl machine
Hamstring machine

2 seperate bathrooms equipped with a loo, hairdryer, 2-in-1 soap and warm water. Water cooler just outside the loo.

Edit:
Pec fly machine is out of order (20 July 22)

author: yu jack
text:
1. The gym is overcrowded with excessive equipment, making it feel cramped and hard to move around.
2. The weighing scale has been broken for years and still hasn‚Äôt been replaced.
3. Staff are almost impossible to reach, making it difficult to get help when needed.
4. Some equipment is frequently out of order, with repairs seemingly always pending.
5. While joining is straightforward, canceling a membership is extremely frustrating. Staff frequently ignore messages, delay responses, and fail to answer calls during office hours, making the process feel intentionally difficult. They often say you need to contact ‚Äúanother department‚Äù for cancellations, but never provide clear contact information, leaving you in the dark about how to end your membership.
6. Each gym is individually owned and managed separately as of what they write on the website, the review above is only for this gym outlet.

If you are looking for a gym with good support, avoid this outlet.

author: Duncan Lim
text: This gym stands out as one of the superior options in the area. Their equipment is sourced from reputable brands like Hammer Strength and Life Fitness, which surpasses the quality of Precor. Even if you happen to forget your access card, their staff can manually check you in, ensuring hassle-free entry. Maintaining cleanliness and hygiene is a top priority here, and the cleaning staff does an excellent job. I would recommend this gym for those in search of a top-notch fitness facility.

author: Audrey L
text: Been gymming here since they opened and maintenance has fallen significantly in the past two years. Open floor area is messy and not cleaned properly. Fans not working, aircon usually kinda hot (sometimes they turn certain units off I presume to save on electricity costs). Toilet is also kinda dirty and smelly. There‚Äôs this new phenomenon where the gym seems to have mistaken itself for a club and working out there can feel like you‚Äôre in a torture camp. Feedbacked to the manager once and to his credit he did lower the volume but turned it back up after an hour.

author: Kathleen Salazar
text:
Staff are nice and the equipment is adequate.

As a girl I‚Äôm looking for hip thrust machines and abductor machine but there weren‚Äôt any here. Just have to make do with the barbells etc. Had a good upper body workout still! Alot of machines but can feel a bit squeezy ONLY A BIT. (but normal in other AFs and ActiveSGs).

author: Shak
text:
I had to cancel my membership, before the first year contract is completed, due to medical reason and the admins had delayed this process with the explanation ‚Äúmanagement decision to review and approve cancellation may take time‚Äù. I have paid subscription for at least 4 months without even entering the facility, out of which 2 months are due to the management delaying to get back to me, and now they ask me to pay 100$ and close. Truly disappointing from such an established brand.

Regarding the facilities itself (Buangkok), when I sign up I was offered 1-hour free PT session, where the trainer taken up my entire hour trying to sell his service than helping me familiarize with basics. I gave this feedback, but not sure if that changes anything. I guess it's just ok ok facilities if you want to do things on your own, and for the first 4 weeks I went there, the equipments were available without waiting between 8 am to 10 am window (don't know about other times)..

Update 05th May 2024: The center had acknowledged that my membership was cancelled after I had paid $100 as early termination fee, however I have noticed in my bank statements that I was charged again for the membership fee in April and May 2024. I had reported this again to their official WhatsApp account in April which they did not respond, and today again where they gave a lame excuse of system issues causing unauthorized charging to my debit card, and I am told the two months fee will be credited back to me. I am glad that I had gone through my statements closely, if I hadn't then Anytime fitness would have continued to charge me.

I hope the anytime fitness upper management take action on this center's unprofessional handling of cancellations.

author: Yuki Kino
text:
earlier today i made a phone call to the buangkok branch to enquire about my brother's membership issue to know more about the problem and honestly speaking i feel that the staff was very unprofessional.
I only called to enquire and just to check on how to the membership works then afterwards i explain on the membership that my brother had and ask on how to cancel. the man on the phone with me had the audacity to mention that i was blaming  the company when i was just purely asking and explaining about my situation.  the audacity of that staff made me so speechless and disappointed as i was only trying to solve the problem on the cancellation of the membership instead of blaming him BUT he was pointing fingers at me.
Not only that, prior before when my brother sign up for this membership at the midtown outlet, the staff who recommended this contract did NOT highlight the important parts of the contract. I understand that it is part of my brother's fault for not reading the contract BUT as a service provider they should be more professional and highlight the important part of the contract, example like the rules on cancelling the membership and the fact that the membership is auto renew monthly.
ultimately, i hope that all the service provider staffs will be more professional when handling their clients by highlighting all the important points in the contract AND explain more in-depth to avoid confusions like this in the future.

text:
Pros: A lot of equipment. Have vendo if you need protein shakes or bars. Many disinfectant sprays on the equipment, also have wet wipes.

Cons: There's no trash bin in the other toilet. Most of the time, the tissue paper is on the floor. So the toilet always looks dirty because of this.

author: lmao xxd
text: A little crowded but nice place to gym at with ample equipments. Gym manager is very nice to talk to and will give advice when needed. The members are generally very friendly and are very willing to share equipments.

author: K O
text: Visiting this as an Australian Anytime Fitness member. Rather small gym but equipment selection is excellent. There was a wide cable machine in an otherwise tight space (Very happy that this was available!). Not easy to social distance within the confines. One major critique I had was how members would maintain the sanitary conditions of the shared equipment. There were baskets with sanitising spray and microfibre towels attached to the machines. The reusing of these towels was what made me feel extremely uncomfortable. (How often are they washed and replaced?) Most other AFs I had visited in Singapore (and in Australia) use disposable wipes. Yes, they aren‚Äôt as environmentally friendly but considering the current pandemic conditions we are in, I suppose that would be a better trade off than the common microfibre towel wipes.

author: Sriram Vijayakumar
text: Training at Anytime Fitness Buangkok has been the best decision. The overall vibe is fantastic. Staff and trainers are extremely friendly. You've got everything you'll ever need. I've only had positive experiences. Amazing, well-equipped, and spotless gym.  I would strongly recommend it!
